{"id":129138,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8xMjkxMzg=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/129138","title":"APT repository is signed using weak digest (SHA-1)","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","severity_rating":"low","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2016-04-08T00:22:56.148Z","submitted_at":"2016-04-08T00:22:56.148Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"reed","url":"/reed","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/132/66d7eadcea16b878bb67bfd697b9542250a801a7_original.jpg/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":17011,"url":"https://hackerone.com/newrelic","handle":"newrelic","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/017/011/eba06abb23bd6c9c7d719ddafb9fa83bd2d66aaa_original./43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/017/011/eba06abb23bd6c9c7d719ddafb9fa83bd2d66aaa_original./fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"profile":{"name":"New Relic","twitter_handle":"newrelic","website":"https://newrelic.com","about":"New Relic's Coordinated Disclosure Program"}},"has_bounty?":false,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2017-02-18T01:44:07.814Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2017-02-18T01:44:07.788Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2017-02-18T01:40:29.491Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"When installing New Relic on a new Ubuntu 16.04 (xenial) machine to test out the beta, I noticed this warning:\n`W: gpgv:/var/lib/apt/lists/apt.newrelic.com_debian_dists_newrelic_Release.gpg: The repository is insufficiently signed by key B60A3EC9BC013B9C23790EC8B31B29E5548C16BF (weak digest)`\n\nThis specifically means that the signature at https://apt.newrelic.com/debian/dists/newrelic/Release.gpg used the SHA-1 digest algorithm.\n\nI downloaded both `Release` and `Release.gpg` and validated this:\n\n```\n| =\u003e gpg -v --verify Release.gpg Release\ngpg: armor header: Version: GnuPG v1.4.11 (GNU/Linux)\ngpg: Signature made Thu Mar 17 12:04:33 2016 CDT\ngpg:                using DSA key 0xB31B29E5548C16BF\ngpg: using PGP trust model\ngpg: Good signature from \"New Relic \u003csupport@newrelic.com\u003e\"\ngpg: WARNING: This key is not certified with a trusted signature!\ngpg:          There is no indication that the signature belongs to the owner.\nPrimary key fingerprint: B60A 3EC9 BC01 3B9C 2379  0EC8 B31B 29E5 548C 16BF\ngpg: binary signature, digest algorithm SHA1\n```\n\nSignatures with that GPG key need to be using SHA-2 or better.\n\nMore information about this problem and the best ways to fix it:\n* https://wiki.debian.org/Teams/Apt/Sha1Removal\n* https://www.debian-administration.org/users/dkg/weblog/48\n* https://juliank.wordpress.com/2016/03/15/clarifications-and-updates-on-apt-sha1/\n* https://askubuntu.com/questions/750133/how-can-i-fix-w-the-repository-is-insufficiently-signed-by-the-key","weakness":{"id":32,"name":"Cryptographic Issues - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2017-03-20T01:40:29.523Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-143985389.84812054,"singular_disclosure_a